---
import CtaButton from '../CtaButton.astro';
import QuizCard from '../QuizCard.astro';

interface VocabularyItem {
  no: number;
  word: string;
  meaning: string;
  example: string;
}

interface Props {
  data: {
    context: string;
    vocabularyItems: VocabularyItem[];
    quizUrl: string;
    quizImage: string;
  };
}

const { data } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="vocabulary-content">
  <h3>3. Key Vocabulary for OET Speaking</h3>

  <h4>Core Vocabulary List (Patient-Centered Language)</h4>
  <p>
    This module focuses on developing students' language skills and clinical communication when discussing {data.context}. To support this learning, the following key vocabulary items will help you communicate more effectively during practice sessions with the chatbot and your classmates. Read and understand them carefully before the class session.
  </p>

  <p>🔑 <strong>15 Key Vocabulary Items</strong></p>

  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table class="vocab-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>No.</th>
          <th>Vocabulary</th>
          <th>Meaning (Simple)</th>
          <th>Example Sentences</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {data.vocabularyItems.map((item) => (
          <tr>
            <td>{item.no}</td>
            <td><strong>{item.word}</strong></td>
            <td>{item.meaning}</td>
            <td>{item.example}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="vocab-phrases">
    <div class="phrases-header">
      <div class="phrases-icon">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"/>
          <path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"/>
          <path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h4>Key Vocabulary and Useful Phrases for Speaking Subtest</h4>
    </div>
    <p>
      You will also learn important vocabulary and useful phrases for the OET speaking subtest.
      The following video explains common verbs and expressions that often appear on the role-play card,
      such as <em>explain, reassure, suggest,</em> and <em>recommend</em>. You will also learn how to
      ask questions politely, give information clearly, and speak in a friendly and professional way
      with patients. By watching this video, you will better understand what to say during the speaking
      test and how to communicate more naturally and confidently.
    </p>
    <p class="phrases-cta-label">Click the following icon to watch it.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <CtaButton href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=foshAXAtzk0" variant="primary" size="md">
        📺 Watch Video
      </CtaButton>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="vocab-exercise">
    <p><strong>✍️ Vocabulary Exercise</strong></p>
    <p>To identify how well your understanding of the vocabulary is, take the following quiz:</p>
    <QuizCard quizUrl={data.quizUrl} quizImage={data.quizImage} label="Vocabulary Quiz" />
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .vocabulary-content h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .vocabulary-content p {
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .section-image {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-image img {
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--card-radius);
  }

  .table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  th, td {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: var(--space-3);
    text-align: left;
  }

  th {
    background: var(--color-primary-50);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  td {
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .vocab-table td:first-child {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .vocab-exercise {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    border-radius: var(--card-radius);
    padding: var(--space-5);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
  }

  .vocab-phrases {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-50), #eff6ff);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-primary-200);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: var(--card-radius);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
  }

  .phrases-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .phrases-icon {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    border-radius: 10px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .phrases-header h4 {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vocab-phrases p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .phrases-cta-label {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4) !important;
    color: var(--color-text-muted) !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
</style>